<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static void insertDeleteInstructions (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &#42; MBB, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &amp; MI, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &#42; &gt; &amp; InsInstrs, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &#42; &gt; &amp; DelInstrs, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinetracemetrics/ensemble">MachineTraceMetrics::Ensemble</a> &#42; TraceEnsemble, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparseset">SparseSet</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/liveregunit">LiveRegUnit</a> &gt; &amp; RegUnits, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetinstrinfo">TargetInstrInfo</a> &#42; TII, unsigned Pattern, bool IncrementalUpdate)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Inserts InsInstrs and deletes DelInstrs.

Incrementally updates instruction depths if requested.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="MBB">basic block to insert instructions in</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="MI">current machine instruction</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="InsInstrs">new instructions to insert in <code>MBB</code></ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="DelInstrs">instruction to delete from <code>MBB</code></ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="TraceEnsemble">is a pointer to the machine trace information</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="RegUnits">set of live registers, needed to compute instruction depths</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="TII">is target instruction info, used to call target hook</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="<a href=&quot;/docs/api/classes/llvm/pattern&quot;>Pattern</a>">is used to call target hook finalizeInsInstrs</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="IncrementalUpdate">if true, compute instruction depths incrementally, otherwise invalidate the trace</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;unsigned, 16&gt;</a> Patterns;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The motivating example is:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     MUL  Other        MUL&#95;op1 MUL&#95;op2  Other</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      \\    /               \\      |    /</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      ADD/SUB      =&gt;        MADD/MSUB</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      (=Root)                (=NewRoot)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The DAGCombine code always replaced MUL + ADD/SUB by MADD. While this is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// usually beneficial for code size it unfortunately can hurt performance</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// when the ADD is on the critical path, but the MUL is not. With the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// substitution the MUL becomes part of the critical path (in form of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MADD) and can lengthen it on architectures where the MADD latency is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// longer than the ADD latency.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For each instruction we check if it can be the root of a combiner</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// pattern. Then for each pattern the new code sequence in form of MI is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// generated and evaluated. When the efficiency criteria (don&#39;t lengthen</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// critical path, don&#39;t use more resources) is met the new sequence gets</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// hooked up into the basic block before the old sequence is removed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The algorithm does not try to evaluate all patterns and pick the best.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This is only an artificial restriction though. In practice there is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// mostly one pattern, and getMachineCombinerPatterns() can order patterns</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// based on an internal cost heuristic. If</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// machine-combiner-verify-pattern-order is enabled, all patterns are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// checked to ensure later patterns do not provide better latency savings.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"></CodeLine>
